Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 04 of Head MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Ischemia' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And 'Localization' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Ischemia area I' tab is enabled
And 'Ischemia area II' tab is enabled
And 'Vascular occlusion' tab is enabled

When I select 'Localization' tab
Then 'Arterial supply area' radio button is enabled
And 'Venous vascular territories' radio button is enabled

And a multiple choice 'Localization cortex/white matter' localizer is enabled

And 'Cortex' checkbox is enabled
And 'White matter' checkbox is enabled

And 'Periventricular' radio button is enabled
And 'Confluent' radio button is enabled
And a multiple choice localizer is enabled

When I select 'Arterial supply area' radio button
Then 'Shape' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Typical areas of infarction' from 'Shape' dropdown menu
Then a multiple selection 'Vascular territory' localizer is enabled

When I select 'Rare territorial infarcts' from 'Shape' dropdown menu
Then 'Multiple small infarcts in different vascular territories' radio button is enabled
And 'Bilateral thalamic infarcts (Percheron)' radio button is enabled
And 'Dorsolateral infarct in medulla oblongata (Wallenberg syndrome)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Venous vascular territories' radio button
Then 'Cortical veins' checkbox is enabled
And 'Internal cerebral veins' checkbox is enabled
And 'Right vein of Labbé' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left vein of Labbé' checkbox is enabled
And 'Right sphenoparietal sinus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left sphenoparietal sinus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cortical veins' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Internal cerebral veins' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Parietal lobe' from 'Localization cortex/white matter' localizer
Then 'Praecuneus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Occipital lobe' from 'Localization cortex/white matter' localizer
Then 'Cuneus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lingual gyrus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Temporal lobe' from 'Localization cortex/white matter' localizer
Then 'Gyrus temporalis transversus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral occipitotemporal gyrus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cerebellum' from 'Localization cortex/white matter' localizer
Then 'Pars intermedia' checkbox is enabled
And 'Superior cerebellar peduncle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle cerebellar peduncle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Inferior cerebellar peduncle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'White matter' checkbox
Then 'Lokalisation white matter' dropdown menu is enabled
